    "body": "## Problem\n\n## Steps to reproduce\n\n```\nseq 1 100 | xargs -I{} printf '\\e[1;34msrc/gen/\\e[0m\\e[1;32mgen_eval_files.lua\\e[0m\\n' | nvim --clean +'lua vim.schedule_wrap(vim.api.nvim_open_term)(0, {})'\n```\n\n<img width=\"1594\" height=\"722\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/79b65013-6ada-480d-9a35-031c3e185dae\" />\n\n\n## Expected behavior\nThe first few lines should be correctly highlighted.\n\n## System info\n\n- Nvim version (nvim -v): `v0.12.0-dev-2217 g7720e52a0b-dirty` neovim/neovim@7720e52a0b\n- Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?: ?\n- Operating system/version: Linux 6.18.7-zen1-1-zen\n- Terminal name/version: kitty\n- $TERM environment variable: `xterm-kitty`\n- Installation: ?\n\n",
